PRIVILEGED & CONFIDENTIAL: ATTORNEY-CLIENT COMMUNICATION

MATTER STRATEGY & STATUS MEMORANDUM
CASE: Acme Solutions Ltd. v. Global Logistics Corp.
COURT: U.S. District Court, Southern District of New York
DOCKET NO: 26-CV-08942-JS
DATE: May 14, 2026

I. EXECUTIVE SUMMARY
This matter involves a high-stakes commercial dispute centered on a failed hardware deployment for a Tier-1 data center project. Plaintiff (Acme) seeks $1.2M in compensatory damages for lost revenue and reputational harm. Defendant (Global Logistics) is relying heavily on an "Unforeseeable Circumstances" defense.

II. KEY WITNESSES & TESTIMONY
1. Sarah Jenkins (Acme CTO): Will testify regarding the critical nature of the hardware delivery timeline and the impact of the 45-day delay on downstream client SLAs.
2. Marcus Thorne (Global Logistics Ops Director): Likely to testify about the "unprecedented" labor strikes at the port and attempts to find alternative shipping routes.

III. EVIDENCE LOG (RECENT DISCOVERY)
- Exhibit A-04: Internal email from Thorne dated Feb 12, 2026, admitting that "shipment delays are likely" but failing to notify Acme until 3 weeks later.
- Exhibit B-12: Port of Long Beach congestion reports showing 90+ vessels at anchor during the relevant period.

IV. TACTICAL STRATEGY
Our primary goal is to invalidate the Force Majeure defense by proving that Global Logistics was aware of the potential delays well in advance and failed to take reasonable mitigatory steps (e.g., air-freighting the critical components).

V. SETTLEMENT ANALYSIS
Defendant has made an initial "nuisance value" offer of $85,000. We have rejected this. Our current counter-settlement floor is $650,000, based on the strength of our IP infringement cross-claim which we may file if negotiations stall.

VI. UPCOMING COURT APPEARANCES
- Hearing on Motion to Compel Discovery: May 28, 2026
- Status Conference with Judge Sullivan: June 12, 2026

VII. BUDGETARY UPDATE
- Total Approved Budget: $250,000.00
- Remaining Funds: $182,500.00
- Estimated Trial Cost: $95,000.00 additional

